  <heading>TBXQ</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Programmable table lookup within each quadword vector segment (merging)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction reads, for each 128-bit destination vector segment,
each element of the corresponding second source (index) vector segment
and uses its value to select an indexed element from the corresponding
first source (table) vector segment.
The indexed table element is placed
in the element of the destination vector that corresponds to the
index vector element. If an index value is greater than or equal to the
number of elements in a 128-bit vector segment
then the corresponding destination vector element is left unchanged.
This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
